Gospel singer, Evang. Dr. Dunni Olanrewaju, popularly known as Opelope Anointing, recently celebrated the 22 years release of super hit and chart buster track, ‘Opelope Anointing’ that brought her into gospel music limelight and gave her success with breakthrough in the ministry and the industry. The celebration organised by the Opelope Anointing Foundation (OAF) with support of Opelope Anointing Fans Club, took place at Ladi-Lak Primary School open field, Bariga. It featured an open air crusade, free healthcare services, free distribution of clothing materials and food items to widows and the less privilege that turned out in large number to participate and partake in the celebration. Highlight of the celebration was early morning special prayer for pregnant women and those seeking the fruit of the womb. Also, the induction of Opelope Anointing Fans Club (OAC) Bariga zone, respectively was held at The Faith Evangelical Church auditorium, Bariga. Ministers of God, gospel artistes and personalities who graced the crusade and celebration includes, HRH, Oba Joel Olonibua, the Oniiropoka of Iropoka Ekiti; Pastor Opeyemi Fatigue (President, OAC); Bishop Faith Sonibare, Pastor James Olukayode (Chairman, PFN Bariga zone), Pastor Joseph Odubote, Ven. Samuel Afolabi (chairman, OAC Ijebu Igbo Zone), Sup. Evang. Adewale Akande (Governor, OAC Ogun State), Engr. Femi Famuyide, (OAC Gen. Secretary), Barr. Kehinde Afolabi (OAC Legal Adviser), Pastor (Mrs.) E. F Alamu (Governor, OAC Oyo State chapter), Barr. Funke Onafowokan, Prophet J. O Iluobe (OAC Director of Admin.) and many others. Opelope Anointing Foundation (OAF) was established in the year 2010 with the purpose of giving back to the society from the abundance of God’s goodness and blessings in the life and ministry of the 62 years old founder and President, Evang. Dr. Dunni Olanrewaju.